achievements.title: Morphological and Topographical Analysis of Nutrient Foramina in Adult Human Tibiae from Rawalpindi Region: A Descriptive Cross-Sectional Study
achievements.description:
We, a team comprising Abdul Haseeb Ahmad (Roll No. 123), Abdul Shehroz (Roll No. 126) Muneeba Tehreem (Roll No. 118), Muqaddas Jabeen (Roll No. 120), Muntaha Khaliq (Roll No. 119), and Abdul Sattar (Roll No. 127), embarked on our very first research project as beginners in the field. While the study was simple in scope, it provided us with invaluable learning and hands-on experience that we deeply cherish.
To read the full article:

achievements.title: Theoretical Foundations of Health Research
achievements.description: Gaining a deeper understanding of the research process was a key part of my academic journey. This logbook details the series of lectures I completed on the theoretical foundations of health research. The course was a fantastic opportunity to learn about research ethics, develop skills in synopsis and manuscript writing, and understand the practical steps of bringing a research project to life.

achievements.title: Developing Professionalism and Leadership Skills
achievements.description: My academic journey has always been about more than just knowledge; it's also about building character. This logbook documents my engagement with the "Professionalism" module, which focused on accountability and professional conduct. The sessions honed my skills and understanding of professional behavior in foundational medical subjects and clinical settings.

achievements.title: Dedication in Medical Education
achievements.description: I was honoured to achieve highest marks in anatomy in whole batch,which reinforced my dedication to learning and inspired me to pursue excellence with even greater enthusiasm

achievements.title: Triumphing Over a Trail of Trials
achievements.description: In a medical Olympaid held by a society in RMU,I got 3rd position in a segment,Trail of Trials,in which my team has to figure out a complex scenario to find out the murderer of a victim.The case presented multiple medical scenarios that pushed me to analyze, connect clues, and reach logical conclusions like in real clinical practice.

achievements.title: My First life-saving experience
achievements.description: In a segment of "Medicine Olympaid",named Code blue,I got a chance to perform CPR on a patient suffering from cardiac arrest.Though I performed it on a mannequin,I learnt that every second counts during cardiac arrest,and CPR can truly mean the difference between life and death.

reflections.title: Leading a team while coping with hard era of exams
reflections.content: During our exam era, I was entrusted with leading a team of 8 members. Balancing my own preparation with guiding the team was demanding, yet it taught me resilience, time management, and the true spirit of leadership.

reflections.title: Breaking the BARRIER of Fear
reflections.content: I delivered a presentation on the anastomoses of the elbow joint. This experience improved my ability to explain complex anatomical relations in a simplified way and boosted my confidence in public speaking.

reflections.title: My First Dissection
reflections.content: My first dissection of the upper limb was an unforgettable experiencefilled with strange yet profound feelings as I carefully explored the human body. Layer by layer, the dissection revealed the intricate arrangement of structures, giving me a thorough knowledge and deeper understanding of human anatomy.

reflections.title: Attending an online webinar on "how to tackle emergency situations "
reflections.content: I attended an online webinar on title" when seconds matter". This experience enhanced my awareness about quick decision-making and the importance of staying calm and systematic during emergencies, skills that are vital in my future medical career.
